## Data for all large schools (>1300 enrollment) schools, not yet announced for 
##  closure as of 2005,  with graduation rates in the middle
## 80th percentile of schools to be closed

replacement_schools_vs_all_failing <- data_join %>% 
  filter(dbn %in% replacement_schools |
         dbn %in% large_failing_schools |
         dbn %in% failing_2005_large_list) %>% 
  select(dbn, year, total_grads_percent_of_cohort) %>% 
  arrange(dbn, year) %>% 
  mutate(data_cat = ifelse(dbn %in% large_failing_schools,
                           "Announced for Closure in 2005",
                              ifelse(dbn %in% replacement_schools,
                               "Small Replacement Schools opened by 2005",
                               "Failing Open Schools in 2005"))) %>% 
  # Picked 2008 as an arbitrary date, just to show what graduation rates were like 
  # for schools that were closed
  filter(!dbn %in% large_failing_schools | year <= 2008) %>% 
  
  # Started at '06 because 2005 had a small sample size of all the schools
  # Data was also kinda wonky but not sure if that's a good reason for excluding
  filter(!dbn %in% replacement_schools | year >= 2006)


# Plot average graduation rates of schools from 2005-2015, subsetted into:
# 1) Closed failing schools 2) Small Replacement Schools 3) Open failing schools
replacement_schools_vs_all_failing %>% 
  group_by(year, data_cat) %>% 
  summarize(avg_grad = mean(total_grads_percent_of_cohort, na.rm =TRUE)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = avg_grad*100, shape = data_cat)) +
  geom_point(aes(shape = data_cat), size = 3) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = "Average Graduation Rates 2005-2015",
       y = "Average Graduation Rate (%)",
       x = "School Year (as of June)",
       caption = "Sources: NYCDOE (2019), NYCDOE (2013), Research Alliance for NYC Schools (2016) \nNotes: Values for the treated group in 2005 were omitted due to too few observations. \n           Values for the pretreatment group were omitted after 2008 due to too few observations.") +
  scale_shape_discrete(name = "", 
                       labels = c("Preatment", 
                                  "Control", 
                                  "Treatment"),
                       guide = guide_legend(reverse = TRUE)) +
   scale_x_continuous(limits = c(2005, 2015), breaks = c(2005, 2010, 2015)) +
   scale_y_continuous(limits = c(30, 80)) +
   theme_classic() +
   theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0, face = "bold"),
         plot.title.position = "plot",
         plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0),
         plot.caption = element_text(hjust = 0, face = "italic", size = 9),
         plot.caption.position = "plot",
         text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman", size = 13))
## Warning: Removed 20 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

# Create a table displaying average graduation rates from 05-15, for each school type
replacement_schools_vs_all_failing %>% 
  group_by(year, data_cat) %>% 
  summarize(avg_grad = mean(total_grads_percent_of_cohort, na.rm =TRUE)) %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from = data_cat, values_from = avg_grad) %>% 
  filter(year > 2004 & year < 2016) %>% 
  clean_names() %>%
  
  # Add YoY Changes
  transform("control_yoy_change" = c(NA, failing_open_schools_in_2005[-1]/failing_open_schools_in_2005[-nrow(.)]-1),
            "treatment_yoy_change" =  c(NA, small_replacement_schools_opened_by_2005[-1]/small_replacement_schools_opened_by_2005[-nrow(.)]-1)) %>% 
  select(year, 
         failing_open_schools_in_2005, 
         control_yoy_change, 
         small_replacement_schools_opened_by_2005, 
         treatment_yoy_change, 
         announced_for_closure_in_2005) %>% 
  
# Create the gt table
  ungroup(year, data_cat)  %>% 
  gt() %>% 
  tab_header(title = "Average Graduation Rates 2005-2015") %>% 
  tab_spanner(label = "Graduation Rates", columns = 2:6) %>% 
  cols_label( "year" = "School Year (as of June)",
              "failing_open_schools_in_2005" = "Control Group",
              "control_yoy_change" = "YoY (C)",
              "announced_for_closure_in_2005" = "Pretreatment",
              "treatment_yoy_change" = "YoY (T)",
              "small_replacement_schools_opened_by_2005" = "Treatment") %>% 
  
  # Align center
  cols_align(align = "center", columns = c(1:6)) %>% 
  
  # Format decimals
  fmt_number(columns = 2:6, decimals = 2)  %>% 
  
  # Replace all NAs with "-" for readability
  fmt_missing(columns = TRUE, missing_text = "-") %>% 
  
  # Format percentage change columns
  fmt_percent(columns = c(3,5), decimals = 1) %>% 
    
  # Format all text to be times new roman and regular weight/style (except for YoY)
  tab_style(style = cell_text(font = "Times New Roman"), 
            locations = list(cells_column_labels(columns = c(1, 2, 4, 6)),
                          cells_body(columns = c(1, 2, 4, 6)), 
                          cells_title(), 
                          cells_column_spanners(spanners = "Graduation Rates")
                          ) 
            ) %>% 
  
  # Format YoY change columns to be times new roman in italics
  tab_style(style = cell_text(font = "Times New Roman", style = "italic"), 
            locations = list(cells_body(columns = c(3,5)),
                             cells_column_labels(columns = c(3,5))
                            )
            ) %>%
  
  # Bold the title
  tab_style(style = cell_text(weight = "bold"),
            locations = cells_title()) %>% 
  
  # Change size
  tab_options(table.width = px(650),
              heading.align = "left",
              heading.border.bottom.style = "hidden",
              heading.title.font.size = 20
              )

data_join %>% 
  filter(year >= 2005,
         year < 2016) %>%
  filter(total_hs_enrollment > 400) %>% 
    # Remove special schools
  filter(lcgschtyp != "TRANSFER SCHOOL",
         lcgschtyp != "SPECIAL EDUCATION",
         lcgschtyp != "SUSPENSION CENTER") %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  summarize(mean = mean(total_hs_enrollment))

data_join %>% 
  filter(year >= 2005,
         year < 2016) %>%
  filter(total_hs_enrollment < 600) %>% 
    # Remove special schools
  filter(lcgschtyp != "TRANSFER SCHOOL",
         lcgschtyp != "SPECIAL EDUCATION",
         lcgschtyp != "SUSPENSION CENTER") %>%
